title: ETX Freeze Issues
text:
Updated: 14 minutes ago
The Smith County Sheriff’s Office has taken a Winona man into custody on a charge of aggravated sexual assault of a child under 14.
Updated: 6 hours ago
|Kassey Jordan, 42, faces three second-degree felony charges, including the fraudulent procession of 10-50 credit or debit cards, fraudulent possession of identification, and possession of a controlled substance. She was also arrested on a Chambers County warrant for burglary of a building. Jason Paul Kramer, 47, of Baytown, is charged with the second-degree felony of possession of a controlled substance and third degree felony of hindering the apprehension or prosecution of a known felon. He was also arrested on a Polk County warrant for engaging in organized criminal activity.
